Effective Date: 2022
At Tramites.gt, we are committed to ensuring the privacy and security of the non-personally identifiable information (non-PII) we collect and use. This document outlines our data protection practices and how we comply with relevant data protection regulations.

1. Data Collection
Tramites.gt collects and uses non-PII data, which includes:
Procedural Information: Detailed descriptions, requirements, steps, and regulations related to over 1600 government procedures.
Institutional Data: Information about various government institutions, their roles, and the services they offer.
Categorical Data: Categorization of procedures and services to facilitate easy navigation and search functionality within the platform.
Usage Metrics: Aggregated, non-PII metrics such as the most viewed procedures, common search terms, and general user interaction patterns with the site.
We do not collect any personally identifiable information (PII) from users.

2. Data Usage
The non-PII data collected by Tramites.gt is used to:
Provide and improve the platform's functionality and user experience.
Facilitate user access to comprehensive procedural information.
Analyze usage patterns to optimize the platform and enhance its performance.
Ensure the security and integrity of the platform.

3. Data Security
We take the following measures to protect the data collected:
Encryption: All data transmitted between users and our servers is encrypted using Secure Socket Layer (SSL) technology.
Access Controls: Access to data is restricted to authorized personnel only, and we implement role-based access controls to ensure that only those with a legitimate need can access specific data.
Data Minimization: We collect only the data necessary for the purposes outlined in this document and ensure that no PII is collected or processed.
Regular Audits: We conduct regular security audits to identify and address potential vulnerabilities in our systems.

4. Data Retention
We retain non-PII data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this document, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. Usage metrics and other aggregated data are stored to help us continually improve the platform.

5. Compliance with Laws
Tramites.gt complies with all relevant data protection laws and regulations, including but not limited to:

General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR): Although primarily applicable in the European Union, we align our data handling practices with GDPR principles to ensure high standards of data privacy and protection.
Ley de Protecci√≥n de la Privacidad de Guatemala: We adhere to the national laws of Guatemala regarding data protection and privacy.
ISO 27001: We follow principles from the International Standards Organization (ISO) 27001 for information security management systems to ensure robust data security practices.

6. User Rights and Choices
Since we do not collect PII, there are no specific actions required by users regarding data privacy rights. However, users can:

Access Information: Freely access the procedural and institutional information provided on the platform.
Opt-Out of Analytics: If users wish to opt-out of the collection of usage metrics, they can do so by contact us at info@redciudadana.org.gt
Contact Us: For any questions or concerns about our data protection practices, users can contact us at info@redciudadana.org.gt

7. Third-Party Services
We do not share non-PII data with third parties except in the following circumstances:

Service Providers: We may share data with third-party service providers who perform services on our behalf, such as hosting and data analytics. These providers are bound by confidentiality agreements and are not permitted to use the data for any other purpose.
Legal Compliance: We may disclose data if required to do so by law or in response to a valid request by a law enforcement or governmental entity.
8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Data Protection Practices document from time to time. We will notify users of any changes by posting the new policy on the Tramites.gt website. Users are advised to review this document periodically for any changes.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions about these Data Protection Practices, please contact us:

Email: info@redciudadana.org.gt
Address: Guatemala, Guatemala
By using Tramites.gt, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to the data protection practices outlined in this document.
